<standOff type="notes4" corresp="#TNV11"><note xml:lang="en" target="icai">The TNV provides a very different list than that found in the IAC, hence why the few common items are included under parallels, not sources. For a full enumeration of the drums and scales for each landscape, see the sources for the commentary. Note also that two of the parallels provide names for the appropriate <q xml:lang="ta-Latn"><hi rend="italic">yāḻ</hi></q> ('lute'), not for the <q xml:lang="ta-Latn"><hi rend="italic">paṇ</hi></q> ('scale'). For whatever reason, Nakkīraṉār only lists a <term xml:lang="ta-Latn"><hi rend="italic">paṇ</hi></term> for <term xml:lang="ta-Latn"><hi rend="italic">pālai</hi></term> and <term xml:lang="ta-Latn"><hi rend="italic">mullai</hi></term>, in which case he does not provide a <term xml:lang="ta-Latn"><hi rend="italic">yāḻ</hi></term>. Where the names where the same, I decided to provide the <term xml:lang="ta-Latn"><hi rend="italic">yāḻ</hi></term> as a parallel. The two seem to occupy a similar function as one of the two music-elements in his list.</note></standOff>
